		<content type="html" xml:base="https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=246989#p246989"><![CDATA[
If only one field has focus at a time it might be preferred to, instead of having a boolean 'fieldHasFocus', have a global 'focusedField' that determines what field has focus (nil could mean nothing has focus). That way you don't have to update the internal state of several instances when focus changes.<br><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>function love.keypressed(key, scancode, isRepeat)-- ...elseif focusedField and focusedField:keypressed(key, isRepeat) then-- ...end</code></pre></div><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>if someField == focusedField then-- someField has focus!end</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=137182">ReFreezed</a> — Wed Mar 09, 2022 10:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
